Gecina Says Clamageran to Step Down as CEO, Cites Differences

-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 
2011-10-04T16:47:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/gecina-says-clamageran-to-step-down-as-ceo-cites-differences.html
Gecina SA (GFC) ’s board said Christophe
Clamageran will step down from his position as chief executive
officer, citing “differences concerning the priorities for the
implementation of Gecina’s strategy.”  The board named Chairman Bernard Michel as its new chairman
and chief executive officer, Gecina said in an e-mailed
statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  